# Prompt Caching: 10x Cheaper LLM Tokens – Article Summary

**Title:** "Prompt caching: 10x cheaper LLM tokens, but how?"
**Author:** Sam Rose
**Date:** December 16, 2025
**Word Count:** 4,441 words

## Overview

This technical deep-dive explains the mechanics behind prompt caching, which reduces input token costs by 90% while improving latency by up to 85% for lengthy prompts.

## Key Sections

### LLM Architecture Fundamentals

The article breaks down how language models function as massive mathematical operations with four main components: tokenizer, embedding, transformer, and output layers. The author notes that "LLMs are surprisingly small" in terms of code, with some modern models requiring only a few hundred lines.

### Tokenization

Text gets converted into integer token IDs. The prompt "Check out ngrok.ai" becomes tokens like `[4383, 842, 1657, 17690, 75584]`. Different models use different tokenizers, and tokenization represents "a trade-off" between granularity and efficiency.

### Embeddings

Tokens transform into n-dimensional vectors representing semantic meaning. Higher dimensions enable more nuanced representations. Position encoding indicates token placement within the prompt.

### Transformer & Attention Mechanism

The attention mechanism calculates how relevant each token is to generating subsequent tokens through weighted combinations using learned matrices (WQ, WK, WV). This allows the model to understand contextual relationships.

### Prompt Caching Explained

The cached data consists of K and V matrices produced during attention calculations. Instead of recalculating these matrices each inference iteration, providers store them for 5-10 minutes and reuse them for matching prompt prefixes, enabling substantial computational savings and cost reduction.

Assistant2025-12-26T22:38:18.705Z

Review: "Prompt Caching: 10x Cheaper LLM Tokens" by Sam Rose (ngrok)

Summary

This is a well-written technical deep-dive explaining how prompt caching works under the hood. It was published December 16, 2025, and clocks in at ~4,400 words.

Strengths

  1. Clear pedagogy - The article builds understanding incrementally, starting from LLM architecture basics (tokenizer → embedding → transformer → output) before explaining caching.

  2. Demystifies LLMs - The observation that "LLMs are surprisingly small" in code (a few hundred lines) helps readers see past the mystique.

  3. Concrete examples - Uses practical examples like showing how "Check out ngrok.ai" tokenizes to [4383, 842, 1657, 17690, 75584].

  4. Gets to the real insight - Explains that what's actually cached are the K (key) and V (value) matrices from attention calculations, not the raw tokens. This is the crucial technical detail most explainers skip.

  5. Practical context - Notes that providers typically cache for 5-10 minutes and that caching only works for matching prompt prefixes.

Key Takeaways

  • 90% cost reduction on input tokens
  • Up to 85% latency improvement for long prompts
  • Caching avoids redundant matrix multiplications in the attention mechanism
  • Only prefix matches benefit (you can't cache the middle of a prompt)

Who Should Read This

Anyone building LLM applications who wants to understand why prompt caching works, not just that it works. Particularly useful for developers optimizing costs with Claude, GPT-4, or similar APIs.

Minor Notes

The article focuses on conceptual understanding rather than implementation specifics for any particular provider. If you need provider-specific guidance (Anthropic, OpenAI, etc.), you'd need supplementary docs.

Overall: Recommended read for developers wanting deeper LLM intuition.

Based on the search results, here's what I found:

## ngrok Blog - Prompt Caching

The ngrok blog features "a far more detailed explanation of prompt caching than anyone asked for." The article is available at ngrok.com/blog/prompt-caching/.

This was a significant project - "Yesterday we launched https://ngrok.ai into early access. Today we're bringing you a deep dive into LLM internals with beautiful visuals" that help users "discover exactly what gets cached to offer you 10x cheaper input tokens."

The blog post explains how prompt caching works in LLMs:
- "We're redoing lots of calculations we don't need to. Most of the matrix multiplications for 'Mary had a little' aren't necessary if you've only just finished processing 'Mary had a', which is how the LLM inference loop works."
- You can avoid these duplicate calculations by "Cache the K and V matrices every iteration" and "Only feed the newest token into the model, not the entire prompt."

The post includes interactive animations to visualize the concepts: "Let's take a look at the grid above again, but this time we'll see it get populated as each new token is produced in the inference loop. Hit play to start the animation."

## Three.js on GitHub

The Three.js library "creates a scene, a camera, and a geometric cube, and it adds the cube to the scene. It then creates a WebGL renderer for the scene and camera, and it adds that viewport to the document.body element. Finally, it animates the cube within the scene for the camera."(no content)Three.js is "a cross-browser JavaScript library and application programming interface (API) used to create and display animated 3D computer graphics in a web browser using WebGL. The source code is hosted in a repository on GitHub."(no content)Three.js was first released by Ricardo Cabello on GitHub in April 2010.(no content)ngrok has 42 repositories available on GitHub, including tools for Node.js integration and Terraform providers.

📝 Write TokenEmbeddingVisualizer.tsx


/Users/scotthandley/Code/2026-krumlov-presentation/src/components/TokenEmbeddingVisualizer.tsx


import { Canvas, useFrame } from '@react-three/fiber'
import { Text, OrbitControls } from '@react-three/drei'
import { useRef, useState, useMemo } from 'react'
import * as THREE from 'three'

// Token IDs from the ngrok blog post
const TOKENS = [75, 305, 284, 887]

// Fake embedding vectors (4 dimensions shown for each token)
const EMBEDDINGS = [
  [4.7, 1.0, 2.7, 3.9],
  [0.5, 1.5, 0.5, 2.7],
  [5.0, 0.5, 3.7, 0.1],
  [0.3, 0.1, 0.5, 0.3],
]

// Colors matching the original
const TOKEN_COLOR = '#fe9a00'
const EMBEDDING_COLOR = '#00bc7d'

interface TokenDisplayProps {
  tokens: number[]
  visible: boolean
  opacity: number
}

function TokenDisplay({ tokens, visible, opacity }: TokenDisplayProps) {
  if (!visible && opacity <= 0) return null

  return (
    <group position={[0, 0, 0]}>
      {/* Opening bracket */}
      <Text
        position={[-3.5, 0, 0]}
        fontSize={0.8}
        color="white"
        anchorX="center"
        anchorY="middle"
        fillOpacity={opacity}
      >
        [
      </Text>

      {/* Token values */}
      {tokens.map((token, i) => (
        <group key={i} position={[-2 + i * 1.8, 0, 0]}>
          <Text
            fontSize={0.6}
            color={TOKEN_COLOR}
            anchorX="center"
            anchorY="middle"
            fillOpacity={opacity}
            font="/fonts/JetBrainsMono-Bold.woff"
          >
            {token}
          </Text>
          {/* Underline */}
          <mesh position={[0, -0.4, 0]}>
            <planeGeometry args={[0.8, 0.05]} />
            <meshBasicMaterial color="#4a4a5a" transparent opacity={opacity * 0.5} />
          </mesh>
          {/* Comma/bracket */}
          <Text
            position={[0.6, 0, 0]}
            fontSize={0.5}
            color="white"
            anchorX="center"
            anchorY="middle"
            fillOpacity={opacity * 0.7}
          >
            {i < tokens.length - 1 ? ',' : ']'}
          </Text>
        </group>
      ))}
    </group>
  )
}

interface EmbeddingCardProps {
  values: number[]
  index: number
  opacity: number
  progress: number
}

function EmbeddingCard({ values, index, opacity, progress }: EmbeddingCardProps) {
  const groupRef = useRef<THREE.Group>(null)

  // Animate the card position and rotation
  const targetX = -2.5 + index * 1.8
  const targetRotation = -0.4

  useFrame(() => {
    if (groupRef.current) {
      // Lerp position
      groupRef.current.position.x = THREE.MathUtils.lerp(
        groupRef.current.position.x,
        targetX,
        0.1
      )
      // Lerp rotation based on progress
      groupRef.current.rotation.x = THREE.MathUtils.lerp(
        0,
        targetRotation,
        progress
      )
    }
  })

  if (opacity <= 0) return null

  return (
    <group ref={groupRef} position={[targetX, 0, 0]}>
      {/* Card background */}
      <mesh position={[0, 0, -0.1]}>
        <planeGeometry args={[1.2, 2.8]} />
        <meshBasicMaterial
          color="#2a2a3a"
          transparent
          opacity={opacity * 0.8}
        />
      </mesh>

      {/* Embedding values stacked vertically */}
      {values.map((val, j) => (
        <Text
          key={j}
          position={[0, 1 - j * 0.7, 0]}
          fontSize={0.35}
          color={EMBEDDING_COLOR}
          anchorX="center"
          anchorY="middle"
          fillOpacity={opacity}
        >
          {val.toFixed(1)}
        </Text>
      ))}
    </group>
  )
}

interface EmbeddingDisplayProps {
  embeddings: number[][]
  visible: boolean
  opacity: number
  progress: number
}

function EmbeddingDisplay({ embeddings, visible, opacity, progress }: EmbeddingDisplayProps) {
  if (!visible && opacity <= 0) return null

  return (
    <group position={[0, 0, 0]} rotation={[0.3, 0, 0]}>
      {/* Opening bracket */}
      <Text
        position={[-4.2, 0, 0]}
        fontSize={0.8}
        color="white"
        anchorX="center"
        anchorY="middle"
        fillOpacity={opacity}
      >
        [
      </Text>

      {embeddings.map((values, i) => (
        <EmbeddingCard
          key={i}
          values={values}
          index={i}
          opacity={opacity}
          progress={progress}
        />
      ))}

      {/* Closing bracket */}
      <Text
        position={[4.2, 0, 0]}
        fontSize={0.8}
        color="white"
        anchorX="center"
        anchorY="middle"
        fillOpacity={opacity}
      >
        ]
      </Text>
    </group>
  )
}

interface SceneProps {
  mode: 'tokens' | 'embeddings'
}

function Scene({ mode }: SceneProps) {
  const [tokenOpacity, setTokenOpacity] = useState(1)
  const [embeddingOpacity, setEmbeddingOpacity] = useState(0)
  const [progress, setProgress] = useState(0)

  // Camera position targets
  const tokenCameraPos = useMemo(() => new THREE.Vector3(0, 0, 8), [])
  const embeddingCameraPos = useMemo(() => new THREE.Vector3(2, 3, 6), [])

  useFrame(({ camera }) => {
    const targetPos = mode === 'tokens' ? tokenCameraPos : embeddingCameraPos

    // Smooth camera movement
    camera.position.lerp(targetPos, 0.05)
    camera.lookAt(0, 0, 0)

    // Animate opacities
    const targetTokenOpacity = mode === 'tokens' ? 1 : 0
    const targetEmbeddingOpacity = mode === 'embeddings' ? 1 : 0
    const targetProgress = mode === 'embeddings' ? 1 : 0

    setTokenOpacity(prev => THREE.MathUtils.lerp(prev, targetTokenOpacity, 0.08))
    setEmbeddingOpacity(prev => THREE.MathUtils.lerp(prev, targetEmbeddingOpacity, 0.08))
    setProgress(prev => THREE.MathUtils.lerp(prev, targetProgress, 0.08))
  })

  return (
    <>
      <ambientLight intensity={0.5} />
      <pointLight position={[10, 10, 10]} />

      <TokenDisplay
        tokens={TOKENS}
        visible={mode === 'tokens'}
        opacity={tokenOpacity}
      />

      <EmbeddingDisplay
        embeddings={EMBEDDINGS}
        visible={mode === 'embeddings'}
        opacity={embeddingOpacity}
        progress={progress}
      />
    </>
  )
}

interface TabButtonProps {
  active: boolean
  onClick: () => void
  color: string
  children: React.ReactNode
}

function TabButton({ active, onClick, color, children }: TabButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      onClick={onClick}
      className={`
        px-4 py-2 font-bold text-sm transition-all duration-200
        border border-slate-600 first:rounded-l-md last:rounded-r-md
        ${active
          ? 'bg-slate-700/50 border-slate-500'
          : 'bg-slate-800/30 hover:bg-slate-700/30'
        }
      `}
      style={{ color: active ? color : '#888' }}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  )
}

export default function TokenEmbeddingVisualizer() {
  const [mode, setMode] = useState<'tokens' | 'embeddings'>('tokens')

  return (
    <div className="w-full max-w-2xl aspect-square bg-dark-bg rounded-2xl border border-slate-700 overflow-hidden">
      {/* Tab buttons */}
      <div className="absolute top-4 left-4 z-10 flex">
        <TabButton
          active={mode === 'tokens'}
          onClick={() => setMode('tokens')}
          color={TOKEN_COLOR}
        >
          Tokens
        </TabButton>
        <TabButton
          active={mode === 'embeddings'}
          onClick={() => setMode('embeddings')}
          color={EMBEDDING_COLOR}
        >
          Embeddings
        </TabButton>
      </div>

      {/* 3D Canvas */}
      <Canvas
        camera={{ position: [0, 0, 8], fov: 50 }}
        style={{ background: '#1a1b26' }}
      >
        <Scene mode={mode} />
        <OrbitControls
          enableZoom={false}
          enablePan={false}
          enableRotate={false}
        />
      </Canvas>

      {/* Attribution */}
      <div className="absolute bottom-3 right-3 text-xs text-slate-500">
        Inspired by{' '}
        <a
          href="https://ngrok.com/blog/prompt-caching"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          className="text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-300 underline"
        >
          ngrok.com
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  )
}

    47→          <Text
    48→            fontSize={0.6}
    49→            color={TOKEN_COLOR}
    50→            anchorX="center"
    51→            anchorY="middle"
    52→            fillOpacity={opacity}
    53→            font="/fonts/JetBrainsMono-Bold.woff"
    54→          >
    55→            {token}
    56→          </Text>
    57→          {/* Underline */}
    58→          <mesh position={[0, -0.4, 0]}>
    59→            <planeGeometry args={[0.8, 0.05]} />
    60→            <meshBasicMaterial color="#4a4a5a" transparent opacity={opacity * 0.5} />
    61→          </mesh>
    62→          {/* Comma/bracket */}
    63→          <Text
    64→            position={[0.6, 0, 0]}
    65→            fontSize={0.5}
    66→            color="white"
    67→            anchorX="center"
    68→            anchorY="middle"
    69→            fillOpacity={opacity * 0.7}
    70→          >
    71→            {i < tokens.length - 1 ? ',' : ']'}
    72→          </Text>
    73→        </group>
    74→      ))}
    75→    </group>
    76→  )
    77→}
    78→
    79→interface EmbeddingCardProps {
    80→  values: number[]
    81→  index: number
    82→  opacity: number
    83→  progress: number
    84→}
    85→
    86→function EmbeddingCard({ values, index, opacity, progress }: EmbeddingCardProps) {
    87→  const groupRef = useRef<THREE.Group>(null)
    88→
    89→  // Animate the card position and rotation
    90→  const targetX = -2.5 + index * 1.8
    91→  const targetRotation = -0.4
    92→
    93→  useFrame(() => {
    94→    if (groupRef.current) {
    95→      // Lerp position
    96→      groupRef.current.position.x = THREE.MathUtils.lerp(
    97→        groupRef.current.position.x,
    98→        targetX,
    99→        0.1
   100→      )
   101→      // Lerp rotation based on progress
   102→      groupRef.current.rotation.x = THREE.MathUtils.lerp(
   103→        0,
   104→        targetRotation,
   105→        progress
   106→      )
   107→    }
   108→  })
   109→
   110→  if (opacity <= 0) return null
   111→
   112→  return (
   113→    <group ref={groupRef} position={[targetX, 0, 0]}>
   114→      {/* Card background */}
   115→      <mesh position={[0, 0, -0.1]}>
   116→        <planeGeometry args={[1.2, 2.8]} />
   117→        <meshBasicMaterial
   118→          color="#2a2a3a"
   119→          transparent
   120→          opacity={opacity * 0.8}
   121→        />
   122→      </mesh>
   123→
   124→      {/* Embedding values stacked vertically */}
   125→      {values.map((val, j) => (
   126→        <Text
   127→          key={j}
   128→          position={[0, 1 - j * 0.7, 0]}
   129→          fontSize={0.35}
   130→          color={EMBEDDING_COLOR}
   131→          anchorX="center"
   132→          anchorY="middle"
   133→          fillOpacity={opacity}
   134→        >
   135→          {val.toFixed(1)}
   136→        </Text>
   137→      ))}
   138→    </group>
   139→  )
   140→}
   141→
   142→interface EmbeddingDisplayProps {
   143→  embeddings: number[][]
   144→  visible: boolean
   145→  opacity: number
   146→  progress: number
   147→}
   148→
   149→function EmbeddingDisplay({ embeddings, visible, opacity, progress }: EmbeddingDisplayProps) {
   150→  if (!visible && opacity <= 0) return null
   151→
   152→  return (
   153→    <group position={[0, 0, 0]} rotation={[0.3, 0, 0]}>
   154→      {/* Opening bracket */}
   155→      <Text
   156→        position={[-4.2, 0, 0]}
   157→        fontSize={0.8}
   158→        color="white"
   159→        anchorX="center"
   160→        anchorY="middle"
   161→        fillOpacity={opacity}
   162→      >
   163→        [
   164→      </Text>
   165→
   166→      {embeddings.map((values, i) => (
   167→        <EmbeddingCard
   168→          key={i}
   169→          values={values}
   170→          index={i}
   171→          opacity={opacity}
   172→          progress={progress}
   173→        />
   174→      ))}
   175→
   176→      {/* Closing bracket */}
   177→      <Text
   178→        position={[4.2, 0, 0]}
   179→        fontSize={0.8}
   180→        color="white"
   181→        anchorX="center"
   182→        anchorY="middle"
   183→        fillOpacity={opacity}
   184→      >
   185→        ]
   186→      </Text>
   187→    </group>
   188→  )
   189→}
   190→
   191→interface SceneProps {
   192→  mode: 'tokens' | 'embeddings'
   193→}
   194→
   195→function Scene({ mode }: SceneProps) {
   196→  const [tokenOpacity, setTokenOpacity] = useState(1)
   197→  const [embeddingOpacity, setEmbeddingOpacity] = useState(0)
   198→  const [progress, setProgress] = useState(0)
   199→
   200→  // Camera position targets
   201→  const tokenCameraPos = useMemo(() => new THREE.Vector3(0, 0, 8), [])
   202→  const embeddingCameraPos = useMemo(() => new THREE.Vector3(2, 3, 6), [])
   203→
   204→  useFrame(({ camera }) => {
   205→    const targetPos = mode === 'tokens' ? tokenCameraPos : embeddingCameraPos
   206→
   207→    // Smooth camera movement
   208→    camera.position.lerp(targetPos, 0.05)
   209→    camera.lookAt(0, 0, 0)
   210→
   211→    // Animate opacities
   212→    const targetTokenOpacity = mode === 'tokens' ? 1 : 0
   213→    const targetEmbeddingOpacity = mode === 'embeddings' ? 1 : 0
   214→    const targetProgress = mode === 'embeddings' ? 1 : 0
   215→
   216→    setTokenOpacity(prev => THREE.MathUtils.lerp(prev, targetTokenOpacity, 0.08))
   217→    setEmbeddingOpacity(prev => THREE.MathUtils.lerp(prev, targetEmbeddingOpacity, 0.08))
   218→    setProgress(prev => THREE.MathUtils.lerp(prev, targetProgress, 0.08))
   219→  })
   220→
   221→  return (
   222→    <>
   223→      <ambientLight intensity={0.5} />
   224→      <pointLight position={[10, 10, 10]} />
   225→
   226→      <TokenDisplay
   227→        tokens={TOKENS}
   228→        visible={mode === 'tokens'}
   229→        opacity={tokenOpacity}
   230→      />
   231→
   232→      <EmbeddingDisplay
   233→        embeddings={EMBEDDINGS}
   234→        visible={mode === 'embeddings'}
   235→        opacity={embeddingOpacity}
   236→        progress={progress}
   237→      />
   238→    </>
   239→  )
   240→}
   241→
   242→interface TabButtonProps {
   243→  active: boolean
   244→  onClick: () => void
   245→  color: string
   246→  children: React.ReactNode
   247→}
   248→
   249→function TabButton({ active, onClick, color, children }: TabButtonProps) {
   250→  return (
   251→    <button
   252→      onClick={onClick}
   253→      className={`
   254→        px-4 py-2 font-bold text-sm transition-all duration-200
   255→        border border-slate-600 first:rounded-l-md last:rounded-r-md
   256→        ${active
   257→          ? 'bg-slate-700/50 border-slate-500'
   258→          : 'bg-slate-800/30 hover:bg-slate-700/30'
   259→        }
   260→      `}
   261→      style={{ color: active ? color : '#888' }}
   262→    >
   263→      {children}
   264→    </button>
   265→  )
   266→}
   267→
   268→export default function TokenEmbeddingVisualizer() {
   269→  const [mode, setMode] = useState<'tokens' | 'embeddings'>('tokens')
   270→
   271→  return (
   272→    <div className="w-full max-w-2xl aspect-square bg-dark-bg rounded-2xl border border-slate-700 overflow-hidden">
   273→      {/* Tab buttons */}
   274→      <div className="absolute top-4 left-4 z-10 flex">
   275→        <TabButton
   276→          active={mode === 'tokens'}
   277→          onClick={() => setMode('tokens')}
   278→          color={TOKEN_COLOR}
   279→        >
   280→          Tokens
   281→        </TabButton>
   282→        <TabButton
   283→          active={mode === 'embeddings'}
   284→          onClick={() => setMode('embeddings')}
   285→          color={EMBEDDING_COLOR}
   286→        >
   287→          Embeddings
   288→        </TabButton>
   289→      </div>
   290→
   291→      {/* 3D Canvas */}
   292→      <Canvas
   293→        camera={{ position: [0, 0, 8], fov: 50 }}
   294→        style={{ background: '#1a1b26' }}
   295→      >
   296→        <Scene mode={mode} />
   297→        <OrbitControls
   298→          enableZoom={false}
   299→          enablePan={false}
   300→          enableRotate={false}
   301→        />
   302→      </Canvas>
   303→

   308→          href="https://ngrok.com/blog/prompt-caching"
